ing Spring Boot changes**\\n\\nI need to consider risks with Spring Boot 3.0, particularly regarding the removal of HttpTrace and potential compile failures due to API drift. It seems I need to make a decision about the setup, which is okay for risk notes. There shouldn’t be any modifications to the repository, but I might explore if deterministic setup is needed instead of a dependency. Also, I wonder if Jackson annotations could issue warnings turning into errors with -Werror, though Gradle doesn't use that flag. I’ll check for metadata issues with Jackson and the Native Image.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra setup is required: the resolved spring-boot-actuator 3.0.0 artifact depends only on spring-boot 3.0.0, and meaningful direct actuator endpoint coverage is reachable without Docker, environment variables, system properties, or additional test dependencies.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The javac failure is caused by Spring Boot 3.0 API drift from the existing 2.6.3 tests, not missing setup; for example HttpTrace APIs were replaced by HTTP exchange APIs and several endpoint constructors changed.\",\n    \"Some optional actuator integrations such as Micrometer metrics, Jackson mapping helpers, database/client health indicators, and web-stack integrations require their own optional libraries, but tests can avoid those optional integration classes unless intentionally covering them.\",\n    \"The documentation recommends spring-boot-starter-actuator for application use, but that is not required to exercise the core spring-boot-actuator artifact directly in reachability tests.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0c162c9cc5a60706016a42e17de7988195be60cb84d1907cef\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1342, "output": 538, "cacheRead": 28160, "cacheWrit